Participants in the recently concluded second School National Milk Programme conference in Mombasa have resolved to establish a Trust Fund to be supported by the county governments.In a seven-point resolution read by agricultural economist James Nyoro, they agreed the programme should be reintroduced in all public schools, through the support of the county and national governments.The conference held at the Pride Inn Paradise Resort on October 27 and 28 was organised by the Kenya Dairy Board. A National School Milk Programme coordination committee will be established and the KDB will facilitate the process, Nyoro said.It was resolved that a five-year strategic plan be established to help implement the programme in all the counties. A policy framework for the programme will be established.